WEBVTT

00:00.734 --> 00:02.201
<i>My name is avery ryan.</i>

00:02.203 --> 00:04.236
<i>I was a victim of cyber crime.</i>

00:04.238 --> 00:07.039
<i>Like you, I posted</i>
<i>on social media,</i>

00:07.041 --> 00:08.607
<i>Checked my bank account</i>
<i>balance online,</i>

00:08.609 --> 00:10.609
<i>Even kept</i>
<i>the confidential files</i>

00:10.611 --> 00:13.045
<i>Of my psychological practice</i>
<i>on my computer.</i>

00:14.614 --> 00:17.549
<i>Then I was hacked,</i>
<i>and as a result,</i>

00:17.551 --> 00:20.119
<i>One of my patients</i>
<i>was murdered.</i>

00:20.121 --> 00:22.588
My investigation into her death
<i>led me to the fbi,</i>

00:22.590 --> 00:25.357
<i>Where I joined a team</i>
<i>of cyber experts</i>

00:25.359 --> 00:28.260
<i>To wage a war against</i>
<i>a new breed of criminal</i>

00:28.262 --> 00:32.164
<i>Hiding on the deep web...</i>

00:32.166 --> 00:35.234
<i>Infiltrating our daily lives</i>
<i>in ways we never imagined...</i>

00:36.736 --> 00:38.737
<i>...Faceless...</i>

00:38.739 --> 00:41.140
<i>Nameless...</i>

00:41.142 --> 00:43.208
<i>Lurking inside our devices,</i>

00:43.210 --> 00:45.411
<i>Just a keystroke away.</i>

00:49.049 --> 00:51.717
(distant siren blaring)

00:51.719 --> 00:53.786
(panting)

00:56.456 --> 00:58.690
(grunts softly)

01:14.841 --> 01:17.576
â™ª

01:42.635 --> 01:44.236
(line ringing)

01:44.238 --> 01:45.737
You've reached raven.
Leave me a message.

01:45.739 --> 01:48.607
Raven, hey, it's me.
It's nelson.

01:48.609 --> 01:50.742
I'm sending you a file,
but just don't open it.

01:50.744 --> 01:53.512
When you get this message, don't
worry about calling me back.

01:53.514 --> 01:55.581
(grunts)

02:09.596 --> 02:11.130
(laughter)

02:11.132 --> 02:13.632
Stop, stop, stop.
Oh, I know.

02:13.634 --> 02:15.634
I will never forget mom's face

02:15.636 --> 02:17.536
When you coughed up
that cricket.

02:17.538 --> 02:19.571
(laughing):
What?!

02:21.241 --> 02:23.909
It was huge. I could feel it
crawling back up my throat.

02:32.485 --> 02:35.454
No.

02:35.456 --> 02:38.290
Don't do it, little brother.
What?

02:38.292 --> 02:41.193
Do not say something mushy
and ruin this.

02:41.195 --> 02:44.663
I love you, francine.

02:44.665 --> 02:45.764
Ew. Ew.

02:45.766 --> 02:47.499
Ugh!
(chuckling)

02:47.501 --> 02:48.834
(phone chimes)

02:48.836 --> 02:51.803
Oh, shoot. I got to go.

02:52.805 --> 02:55.507
Do you mind if I put this
on my credit card

02:55.509 --> 02:56.942
And you just give me cash?

02:56.944 --> 02:59.511
'cause I do not have time
to run to an atm.

02:59.513 --> 03:02.814
Where the heck is my wallet?

03:02.816 --> 03:04.850
I have so much
junk in here.

03:04.852 --> 03:07.486
Seriously, I have
to clean out my bag.

03:13.826 --> 03:15.928
Taylor pettis?

03:16.930 --> 03:19.364
Oh, my god,
that's him, isn't it?

03:19.366 --> 03:21.600
Wait, daniel. Wait. What are
you...? Why are you going?

03:21.602 --> 03:24.203
I want to talk to him.
What? No. Why?
Just, let's just go.

03:24.205 --> 03:26.371
He killed our parents,
and I want to talk to him.

03:26.373 --> 03:28.440
Daniel, no. Please?

03:33.880 --> 03:36.615
I can't believe
they let you out.

03:36.617 --> 03:38.584
I was hoping for
the death penalty.

03:38.586 --> 03:40.586
Did you know that?
Excuse me.

03:40.588 --> 03:42.988
Can I get a
to-go container?
You don't
want to chat?

03:45.325 --> 03:46.858
What do you want from me?

03:46.860 --> 03:48.627
I came over
here to give you

03:48.629 --> 03:50.596
A little piece of advice.

03:50.598 --> 03:52.364
Don't do anything wrong.

03:52.366 --> 03:53.966
For 17 years,
I was afraid of you,

03:53.968 --> 03:56.635
Even when you were locked away,
but you know what?

03:56.637 --> 03:58.637
Now I'm an fbi agent,
and you are just

03:58.639 --> 04:00.606
A scumbag criminal.

04:00.608 --> 04:02.641
You know what that means?

04:02.643 --> 04:05.410
I'm your worst nightmare.

04:05.412 --> 04:07.346
You do anything illegal,

04:07.348 --> 04:11.383
And I will bust your ass
back to prison for life!

04:11.385 --> 04:14.720
You can hide, lay low,
move away, and I will still

04:14.722 --> 04:17.522
Come after you.

04:18.758 --> 04:22.728
(sighs)

04:22.730 --> 04:24.730
Ryan:
<i>Listen up, we got a new case.</i>

04:24.732 --> 04:27.666
<i>Tabloid gossip amplified.</i>

04:27.668 --> 04:29.368
Each one of these people woke up

04:29.370 --> 04:30.836
This morning
the victim of a hack.

04:30.838 --> 04:32.904
Recordings
of personal conversations

04:32.906 --> 04:34.606
They had were leaked online.

04:34.608 --> 04:36.675
All right, I got a congressman,
a ceo, an accountant.

04:36.677 --> 04:37.643
Krumitz:
And a grocery store clerk?

04:37.645 --> 04:39.378
Mundo:
It doesn't add up.

04:39.380 --> 04:41.413
There's no apparent connection
between any of these victims.

04:41.415 --> 04:43.682
Well, this is a specific
and unusual hack.

04:43.684 --> 04:44.916
No e-mails, no
personal photos.

04:44.918 --> 04:46.918
Just audio files.
And none
of the victims'

04:46.920 --> 04:50.355
Devices collected revealed
any evidence of an intrusion.

04:50.357 --> 04:51.790
Krumitz, I want you to run

04:51.792 --> 04:54.293
A waveform analysis
on those audio files.

04:54.295 --> 04:55.861
Where, when,
how were they recorded?

04:55.863 --> 04:58.297
There's got to be a connection.
Nelson?

04:59.299 --> 05:00.799
Where's nelson?

05:02.535 --> 05:05.637
Sorry. I... I thought
I mentioned this. Nelson called.

05:05.639 --> 05:07.939
He fell asleep on the metro
and missed his stop,

05:07.941 --> 05:09.808
So he should be here...
Any minute now?

05:09.810 --> 05:11.510
Daniel, I'll help you
with the audio files.

05:11.512 --> 05:13.945
Ryan:
Our target
has an agenda.

05:13.947 --> 05:17.049
We need to know what that is
so we can find them.

05:26.693 --> 05:28.694
Woman:
It's easy to steal from them.

05:28.696 --> 05:30.662
It started with me
taking a few dollars

05:30.664 --> 05:32.364
From the register every shift.

05:32.366 --> 05:34.333
Man:
I sometimes imagine killing him.

05:34.335 --> 05:36.401
I'm afraid
I'll really do it someday.

05:36.403 --> 05:39.538
Man 2:
I feel so guilty every time
I look into my wife's eyes

05:39.540 --> 05:40.939
And tell her I was working late

05:40.941 --> 05:42.874
When really
I was with another woman.

05:42.876 --> 05:45.010
Woman 2: He was 15.
I was his math teacher.

05:45.012 --> 05:46.945
I never intended
to have sex with him.

05:46.947 --> 05:48.780
It just happened.

05:48.782 --> 05:50.549
Sounds like a confession.

05:50.551 --> 05:51.783
Bring down the volume
on the main track

05:51.785 --> 05:53.085
And pull up the room tone.

05:55.521 --> 05:58.690
(water flowing)

05:58.692 --> 06:00.559
Is that the sound of water?
Krumitz:
Yep.

06:00.561 --> 06:02.794
It's the only sound all
the audio files have in common.

06:02.796 --> 06:05.097
So, they were all recorded
in the same place.

06:06.599 --> 06:08.767
There's hesitation,
moments of defensiveness,

06:08.769 --> 06:10.802
And ultimately, relief.

06:10.804 --> 06:12.104
These aren't confessions.

06:12.106 --> 06:13.505
They're sessions.

06:13.507 --> 06:15.140
They're therapy sessions.

06:15.142 --> 06:18.076
Our victims' confidential files
were hacked.

06:18.078 --> 06:19.811
And they all have
the same therapist.

06:19.813 --> 06:22.114
I'm gonna make a call,
get an address.

06:22.116 --> 06:23.548
Elijah, krumitz, you're with me.

06:23.550 --> 06:25.450
Let's go.

06:25.452 --> 06:28.453
Uh, I don't know
what nelson's up to

06:28.455 --> 06:29.755
Or what you know
about where he is,

06:29.757 --> 06:31.757
But I think it would
be a very good idea

06:31.759 --> 06:33.525
If he were here
when we got back.

06:33.527 --> 06:35.627
Me, too.
Yeah.

06:37.029 --> 06:39.798
(sighs heavily)

06:39.800 --> 06:41.733
You've reached brody nelson.

06:41.735 --> 06:42.968
Leave me a message.

06:42.970 --> 06:45.504
Nelson, it's me <i>again.</i>

06:45.506 --> 06:47.072
I'm officially worried.

06:47.074 --> 06:49.141
Call me.

06:52.812 --> 06:54.846
Screw it.

07:01.788 --> 07:03.922
There you are, nelson.

07:03.924 --> 07:06.825
<i>Agent ryan, those nine victims</i>
<i>were all patients</i>

07:06.827 --> 07:08.527
<i>Of a dr. Richard chan.</i>

07:08.529 --> 07:10.462
<i>350 mass avenue northeast.</i>

07:10.464 --> 07:11.863
Ryan:
<i>Thank you.</i>

07:11.865 --> 07:13.932
The door's ajar.

07:26.879 --> 07:29.047
Ryan:
There's our sound of water.

07:29.049 --> 07:30.715
There was a struggle.

07:30.717 --> 07:32.984
(camera shutter clicking)

07:59.612 --> 08:00.812
Ramirez:
Nelson!

08:00.814 --> 08:02.047
I'm over here!

08:02.049 --> 08:04.015
Come on!

08:04.017 --> 08:05.851
Cut me loose. I'm tied up.

08:06.886 --> 08:08.553
Come on!

08:08.555 --> 08:10.055
What happened?

08:10.057 --> 08:11.590
Are you okay?

08:11.592 --> 08:13.859
Did you get the file I sent?
Yes, I got the file.

08:13.861 --> 08:15.660
What are you up to, nelson?

08:15.662 --> 08:17.629
Did you get in
a fight or something?

08:17.631 --> 08:19.865
(panting)

08:21.000 --> 08:23.835
It's gone!
Everything is... Is gone.

08:23.837 --> 08:26.171
What are you talking about?!

08:26.173 --> 08:29.007
You sure you got
the file I sent?
Yes, I have
the file you sent me.

08:29.009 --> 08:31.243
I have it
right here.
Okay, good.

08:31.245 --> 08:33.912
But, nelson, there is fbi
protocol that we need to follow.

08:33.914 --> 08:35.180
They take this stuff seriously.

08:35.182 --> 08:37.716
If this isn't for a case,

08:37.718 --> 08:39.718
You could go to jail,
and I could, too,

08:39.720 --> 08:41.086
Because you've made
me an accomplice.

08:41.088 --> 08:42.521
All right.

08:42.523 --> 08:45.056
So, I'm gonna ask you
again, what is going on?

08:45.058 --> 08:46.791
Look, I can't tell you,
all right?

08:46.793 --> 08:48.827
I have to speak to avery.

08:49.929 --> 08:51.630
Unbelievable.

08:55.968 --> 08:57.769
It was a match.

08:57.771 --> 08:59.070
The print lifted
from that hourglass

08:59.072 --> 09:00.872
We collected at
dr. Chan's office.

09:00.874 --> 09:03.174
Did you get a name in afis?

09:03.176 --> 09:06.912
Actually, was an fbi database,
a reference print.

09:06.914 --> 09:09.047
It was mine.

09:09.049 --> 09:10.148
You don't seem surprised.

09:10.150 --> 09:12.317
That hourglass
caught my eye.

09:12.319 --> 09:15.720
I had the same one on my desk
when I was a psychologist--

09:15.722 --> 09:16.988
Until it went missing.

09:16.990 --> 09:18.189
Avery, that was a long time ago.

09:18.191 --> 09:20.025
You don't think
it was the same one?

09:20.027 --> 09:21.026
But you can't argue
with evidence.

09:21.028 --> 09:23.161
My print was on that glass,

09:23.163 --> 09:24.796
Even though
I didn't touch anything

09:24.798 --> 09:26.298
At the crime scene,
so either

09:26.300 --> 09:27.966
It's the same one,
or someone went

09:27.968 --> 09:30.001
To a lot of trouble
to plant my print.

09:30.003 --> 09:31.903
Sifter:
I get the feeling
you know something

09:31.905 --> 09:33.905
More than
what you're telling us.

09:33.907 --> 09:35.740
I don't know what I know, simon.

09:35.742 --> 09:38.109
Avery, four more recordings
were released online.

09:38.111 --> 09:41.179
Someone's also leaked
the details of dr. Chan's

09:41.181 --> 09:42.581
Murder investigation.

09:42.583 --> 09:46.651
Your personal involvement could
compromise this investigation.

09:46.653 --> 09:50.255
So, at the very least, tell
me what you think you know.

09:50.257 --> 09:52.324
Avery, I need to talk to you.

09:52.326 --> 09:53.825
Nelson, you're hurt.

09:53.827 --> 09:54.993
What's happened?
I'm fine.

09:54.995 --> 09:56.161
It's-it's not important.

09:56.163 --> 09:58.096
Can we talk? Alone?

09:58.098 --> 09:59.931
Excuse me.
All right.

10:02.101 --> 10:04.102
Where have you been?
What is going on?

10:04.104 --> 10:05.670
I need your cell phone.

10:05.672 --> 10:06.871
Why?

10:06.873 --> 10:08.106
It's important.

10:10.610 --> 10:13.011
Is your personal
laptop here?

10:13.013 --> 10:15.780
No, I left it at home. Why?

10:15.782 --> 10:17.749
Someone is spying on you.

10:17.751 --> 10:19.050
How do you know that?

10:19.052 --> 10:22.087
Because <i>I</i> was spying on you.

10:22.089 --> 10:24.055
My first week here,

10:24.057 --> 10:27.292
That your psychology practice
was hacked,

10:27.294 --> 10:29.294
And how you hadn't
found the guy.

10:29.296 --> 10:31.062
Well, it stuck with me.

10:31.064 --> 10:33.164
I was a behavioral
psychologist.

10:33.166 --> 10:35.700
I had a practice in new york.

10:35.702 --> 10:38.970
And then, one day, all my
patients' files were stolen

10:38.972 --> 10:41.139
From my computer,

10:41.141 --> 10:44.075
And all their
secrets went public.

10:44.077 --> 10:47.278
I was trying to solve
the unsolvable case.

10:47.280 --> 10:48.880
I saw it as a challenge,

10:48.882 --> 10:50.982
So I went digging
on the deep web.

10:50.984 --> 10:52.283
Nelson,

10:52.285 --> 10:54.285
You broke the conditions
of your parole.

10:54.287 --> 10:56.021
Look, I know. I figured

10:56.023 --> 10:58.356
Whoever hacked you had to keep
the files he stole somewhere.

10:58.358 --> 11:01.793
Just not on a personal device,
but the safest place.

11:02.828 --> 11:04.829
Are you telling me...

11:04.831 --> 11:06.898
You found my files?

11:06.900 --> 11:09.167
Yes.
But the hacker

11:09.169 --> 11:11.369
Has new information about you.
Current documents, photos.

11:11.371 --> 11:14.105
Even has recordings
of your phone conversations.

11:14.107 --> 11:17.909
The fbi runs vulnerability
testing quarterly.

11:17.911 --> 11:19.744
Last month,
they scanned all my devices.

11:19.746 --> 11:21.079
They're clean.
I know.

11:21.081 --> 11:23.314
Which is why I didn't come
to you right away.

11:23.316 --> 11:25.016
I wanted to confirm it.

11:25.018 --> 11:26.351
And I did.

11:26.353 --> 11:27.919
Last night.

11:27.921 --> 11:32.757
<i>On your home laptop attached</i>
<i>to a personal video file.</i>

11:38.864 --> 11:41.066
<i>I downloaded</i>
<i>the malicious code.</i>

11:41.701 --> 11:42.701
I have it right here.

11:42.703 --> 11:43.802
Come on.

11:45.838 --> 11:47.839
Ah, perfect timing.

11:47.841 --> 11:51.176
I just I.D.'d the remote access
trojan on dr. Chan's computer.

11:51.178 --> 11:53.278
Complete control
of the device.

11:53.280 --> 11:54.946
He had access to
the doctor's files

11:54.948 --> 11:56.181
And could
remotely turn

11:56.183 --> 11:57.816
The computer's
microphone on and off.

11:57.818 --> 11:59.117
I couldn't identify
the rat at the scene

11:59.119 --> 12:00.418
Because it was
an unknown exploit.

12:00.420 --> 12:03.088
My guess is it was created
by an old-school hacker.

12:03.090 --> 12:05.223
Even today, it's pretty
impressive work.

12:05.225 --> 12:09.127
This is it.
Dude, what happened to you?
Why are you bleeding?

12:09.129 --> 12:11.863
And where the hell did you find
that code? That's it.

12:11.865 --> 12:14.032
That's the code I just found
on chan's computer.

12:14.034 --> 12:16.267
That's how our target
was able

12:16.269 --> 12:17.936
<i>To open up the microphone</i>
<i>on dr. Chan's</i>

12:17.938 --> 12:19.738
<i>Computer and listen in.</i>

12:19.740 --> 12:21.072
Woman:
<i>My husband will divorce me.</i>

12:21.074 --> 12:22.507
Man:
<i>I sometimes imagine</i>
<i>killing him.</i>

12:22.509 --> 12:26.077
<i>I'm afraid</i>
<i>I'll really do it someday.</i>

12:26.079 --> 12:28.213
Krumitz:
<i>Then our target</i>
<i>must have recorded the sessions</i>

12:28.215 --> 12:29.848
<i>On his own device.</i>

12:29.850 --> 12:31.916
Nelson just discovered it
on my laptop.

12:31.918 --> 12:33.918
Wait, what?
Yeah, it's been there
for a while.

12:33.920 --> 12:36.187
It means whoever hacked
dr. Chan is the same black hat

12:36.189 --> 12:37.288
Who hacked me

12:37.290 --> 12:39.090
All those
years ago.

12:40.226 --> 12:42.427
He's back.

12:45.965 --> 12:52.170
